org.openhubframework.openhub.core.configuration

Class ConfigurationItemProducer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openhubframework.openhub.core.configuration.ConfigurationItemProducer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.springframework.beans.factory.config.BeanPostProcessor

    public class ConfigurationItemProducer
extends Object
implements org.springframework.beans.factory.config.BeanPostProcessor
    Factory hook that allows to inject ConfigurationItem marked by ConfigurableValue into bean instances, e.g. checking for marker interfaces or wrapping them with proxies. By default ConfigurationItemImpl is provided as configuration item.
    Since:
    2.0
    Author:
    Tomas Hanus
    See Also:
    resolveKey(Field), createConfigurationItem(Class, String, ConfigurationService)

      • resolveKey

        protected String resolveKey(Field field)
        Resolves effective key of configuration item from ConfigurableValue annotation. It ConfigurableValue.key() is not provided, effective parameter name is build from the name of class of field and field name.
        Parameters:
        field - that is marked with ConfigurableValue
        Returns:
        effective key name to lookup
